  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is discussed throughout the assessment narrative and was performed at the campaign level; individual validation result records capture comparison metrics and agreement statistics. Aleatory uncertainty arising from pump manufacturing variability, blood rheology donor-to-donor variation, and operating condition tolerances is described qualitatively in the assessment report but is not formally linked to each validation result node. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed, 6 not assessed. Decision: Accepted conditional on sponsor commitment to close credibility gaps prior to IDE submission.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Low",
  "couName": "VAD use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-absolute-threshold",
