      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Transient impeller-volute interaction — pressure fluctuation amplitude",
      "description": "Blade-passing frequency pressure fluctuation amplitudes from unsteady CFD compared against dynamic pressure transducer measurements at 4 circumferential locations. CFD over-predicts fluctuation amplitude by 18–31% at all measurement locations, attributed to simplified volute geometry and turbulence model limitations. Aleatory uncertainty from pump assembly tolerances affecting impeller-volute gap is noted in the discussion section but not quantified in a linked UQ artifact.",
      "comparisonMetric": "Fluctuation amplitude over-prediction: 18–31%",
      "agreementAssessment": "Marginal — systematic over-prediction suggests model form gap"
    },
    {
