      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Non-Newtonian blood viscosity model sensitivity validation",
      "description": "Carreau-Yasuda non-Newtonian viscosity model compared against Newtonian approximation across hematocrit range 35–45%. Hemolysis index sensitivity to viscosity model choice is quantified via parameter sweep. The 10% hematocrit range introduces approximately ±9% variation in predicted NIH. This sensitivity study constitutes a form of uncertainty characterization and is linked as a formal UQ artifact.",
      "comparisonMetric": "NIH sensitivity to hematocrit range: ±9%",
      "agreementAssessment": "Informative — confirms non-Newtonian effects are non-negligible at low shear",
